      <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-semibold mb-3">Open when ahead, close when behind — positional play wins games</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The board isn't just a canvas for words — it's contested territory. Every tile placed opens lanes and blocks others. When you're leading, open the board to maintain pressure. When behind, lock it down and force tight plays. Knowing when to sacrifice 10 points to deny your opponent a Triple Word is what makes strategy players dangerous.</p>
